ISSUE #1: Admin Role Escalation via Role Parameter
Field	Value
Severity	CRITICAL
Location	src/server/rbac.ts + all role checks
CVSS Score	9.1 (Critical)
Problem:
The requireRole() function at line 25 checks user.role !== role but allows admins (!user.isAdmin) to bypass the check. However, there is no secondary guard against a non-admin user spoofing themselves as admin if they can access /admin operations OR if the client can pass an adminRole in updateCurrentUser.

Test the attack: A creator could call any admin-only action by crafting a request that claims role: "admin" if:

Wasp's context validation doesn't strip the role field, OR
Wasp's session serialization allows role modification
Exploit Scenario:
A creator modifies their JWT or session to set role="admin" and calls getAdminCreatorQueue to inspect all profiles, then calls adminApproveVideo for a competitor's application to block them.

Root Cause:
Role enforcement relies entirely on Wasp's context.user object. If a client can manipulate the JWT (via localStorage XSS), they gain admin access. Additionally, updateCurrentUser in user/operations.ts does not explicitly forbid role changes—the only protection is the schema allowlist in updateCurrentUserSchema, but this relies on runtime validation.

